inlineContent.text: A pointer to the secondary status result that provides additional information in case of failure.
A set of attributes, given by their OID, that a mechanism must have in order to appear in the results. See Mechanisms and Authentication in
for a list of possible values.
A set of attributes, given by their OID, that the mechanism must not have in order to appear in the results. See Mechanisms and Authentication in
for a list of possible values.
A set of attributes, given by their OID, that the mechanism must know about, but not necessarily have, in order to appear in the results. See Mechanisms and Authentication in
for a list of possible values.
A pointer the function uses to return a new set of mechanisms that meet the given criteria. Release the set’s memory using a call to
after you are done using it.

abstract.text: Evaluate return values that most GSS-API functions use to indicate the outcome of an operation.
A pointer to a descriptor that manages an array of OID descriptors.
A pointer to an immutable descriptor manages an array of OID descriptors.
Returns a human-readable name and description of a mechanism attribute.
Returns the list of supported underlying security mechanisms.
Returns the set of mechanisms that fulfill the given criteria.
Returns the supported attributes for one or all mechanisms.
Returns the GSS-API mechanism identifier for a given Simple Authentication and Security Layer (SASL) protocol name.
Returns the Simple Authentication and Security Layer (SASL) protocol name for a given GSS-API mechanism.
Releases the memory associated with an OID set.
Provide a security mechanism for your implementation.
A pointer for accessing and manipulating data of a specific type.
